\ul\b\i\fs24 2.Un-installation of older versions of this patch\par
\ulnone\b0\i0\fs20\par
Although not absolutely necessary, the \cf2 "m2_res" folder \cf0 should be deleted from your Mapper2 installation folder.  If present, the "\cf2 m2_res_README.rtf" and "m2_res_change.log" can also be deleted.\cf0\par
\par
\par
\ul\b\i\fs24 3. Installation\par
\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li360\ulnone\i0\fs20 Step 1.\tab\i Extract to the Mapper\i0\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\li360\b0 Double-click the "Mapper2_High_Resolution_Patch_v3.0.2.exe". Click the [Browse] button and find your Mapper2 installation folder (usually "C:\\Program Files\\BlackIsle\\Fallout 2 Mapper\\"). Click [Extract], the extraction window will disappear once complete.\par
\ul\i\fs18 Note\ulnone : If you have installed a previous version of this patch, you may be asked to overwrite some of the files listed above. Answer YES to overwrite files.\ul\par
\ulnone\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li360\b\i0\fs20 Step 2.\tab\i Patch "mapper2.exe" to load "m2_res.dll"\i0\par
\i       \ul\b0\fs18 Note:\ulnone  If you have installed a previous version of this patch, you can skip this step and proceed to Step 3.\b\fs20\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\li360\b0\i0 Once extraction is finished, open your Mapper2 installation folder and Double-Click the "m2_res_patcher.exe".  A Message-box will appear asking if you want to patch the "mapper2.exe". Click the [OK] button to continue. You should then see the message "mapper2.exe was patched successfully".\par
If you ever want to remove this patch, you can do so by running "m2_res_patcher.exe" again and following the prompts.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li360\b Step 3.\tab\i Set the screen resolution in-game\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\li360\b0\i0 Start the Mapper. From the top menu select [Settings], Click the [Screen Settings] button to open the Screen Settings Window. Select your resolution from the list provided, you may also want to adjust the output colours to 16 or 32 bit to overcome palette issues with current versions of the Windows Operating System. When your finished click the [Done] button. You will then be given the option to restart the Mapper to apply the new settings. Click [Yes] to restart the game.\par
\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\fi-360\li360\b Other \i Options\b0\i0\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\li360 You can manually set an unlisted resolution by clicking the small windows labelled 'Width' and 'Height'.\par
You can cycle through the Iface-bar Side Art options by clicking the example image provided.\par
\pard\nowidctlpar\par
